Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.08,0:00:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to another edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.42,0:00:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.76,0:00:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This month we will see examples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.63,0:00:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of what young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.06,0:00:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world\Nhave done to seek\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.50,0:00:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kingdom first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.47,0:00:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Also,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.47,0:00:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you will meet a brother \Nwho got into a lot of trouble \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,early in his life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.51,0:00:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did the truth help him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.21,0:00:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to straighten out his life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to his story. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.22,0:00:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We will also visit \Na language course in Ecuador. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.62,0:00:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it like \Nto learn a new language \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.43,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand our ministry? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We will find out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.26,0:00:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the March program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.94,0:00:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.42,0:01:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My theme for this month’s broadcast is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.99,0:01:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Young Ones\N—Build Your Future With Jehovah!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do, \N1 Timothy 6:19 assures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.97,0:01:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will \N‘safely treasure up for yourself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.31,0:01:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,a fine foundation for the future,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.14,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will \N“get a firm hold on the real life.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.58,0:01:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, we will be directing \Nmany of our comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.85,0:01:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,directly to you dear young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.99,0:01:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, if we think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us figuratively \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.13,0:01:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,are very young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:02:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to eternity\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.04,0:02:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—how long we hope to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in a sense, \Nour comments during this broadcast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.38,0:02:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,have application to all of us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.01,0:02:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I am so thankful to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.89,0:02:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that positive peer pressure \Nwas put on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.66,0:02:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to enter the pioneer ministry \Nright out of high school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.96,0:02:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What a blessing and a protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to enter \Nthe regular pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.30,0:02:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at age 17 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.54,0:02:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be able to go to Bethel at 18. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.97,0:02:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though there was considerable \Nworldly pressure put on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.78,0:02:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue university education, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.85,0:02:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so happy that with Jehovah’s help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.22,0:02:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to build my future \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.89,0:02:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.89,0:02:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, I have no regrets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is always true of young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.03,0:03:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who serve Jehovah from their hearts\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—they have no regrets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you will enjoy \Nthese expressions from young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who are building \Ntheir future with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I started pioneering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really nervous that I wouldn’t be able \Nto get my time in every month.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.92,0:03:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a bit hard when I started pioneering \Nbecause I didn’t have a car.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.90,0:03:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My boss, \Nhe didn’t give me part-time work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.30,0:03:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it really hard \Nto balance schoolwork \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.60,0:03:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and pioneering \Nat the same time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My biggest struggle was fear of man, \Nso that really hindered me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wasn’t very good \Nat talking to people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.31,0:03:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a good routine was a struggle.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.21,0:03:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother and I are \Nthe only ones in the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My family didn’t understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.18,0:03:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,why we wanted to go preaching.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.02,0:03:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t think \Nthat I’d make a good pioneer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had Type 1 diabetes \Nsince I was five. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.16,0:04:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was always worried \Nabout whether or not \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.30,0:04:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I could balance that health condition \Nwith pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The challenges \Ndon’t seem that big now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.23,0:04:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but back at that time \Nthey were a really big deal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.97,0:04:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But the coolest thing \Nwas how Jehovah helped me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.64,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer to Jehovah \Nhelped me overcome my fears.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My family was \Na massive help from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.71,0:04:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because my dad was the one \Nwho first encouraged me to pioneer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.58,0:04:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when I did start pioneering, \Nhe promised that I would have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.99,0:04:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the full support of my family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.89,0:04:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When I spoke to brothers and sisters \Nwho spent their youth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.86,0:04:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the full-time service \Nthat really helped me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was really encouraging, \Nand it really motivated me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to want to make my own memories \Nand my own experiences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.30,0:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So there were \Npractical things I could do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.54,0:04:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t have a car; \NI just walked or I caught the bus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.91,0:04:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to work out \Nwhat my priorities were first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.54,0:04:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to find out how many hours \Nwould I have to go witnessing every week. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:04:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I just sat down \Nand I looked at every day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and planned out which days \NI could go witnessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which days I had to go to school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and also allocated time \Nso that I could do my homework and study.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.92,0:05:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a schedule \Nwas really good \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.69,0:05:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because I could see it \Nall out in front of me,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could see \Nthat the hour requirement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.70,0:05:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was actually attainable, \Nso that made it a lot less daunting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.57,0:05:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I first set short-term goals of pioneering \Nin the special months of activity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.77,0:05:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I was able \Nto begin continuous auxiliary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and then eventually \NI started regular pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.14,0:05:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the best things I did \Nto prepare myself for pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was to auxiliary pioneer beforehand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.48,0:05:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It really set me up \Nto be able to overcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,any challenges \Nthat I faced while I was pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.15,0:05:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about Malachi 3:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.79,0:05:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I trusted in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.79,0:05:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but this was my chance \Nto test him out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.33,0:05:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed, \Nput my trust in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.96,0:05:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and put my application in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After my form \Nwas in for pioneering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.57,0:05:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother, with time, \Na brother called me and offered me work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I had unemployment \Nfor three months, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.01,0:06:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which wasn’t a good time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.28,0:06:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But during that time, \NI had Jehovah as my main focus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.58,0:06:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he supported me, \Nand he didn’t let me down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking brothers and sisters to come \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and work with me, \Nmaybe on days that I knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.99,0:06:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wouldn’t get as much support, \Nreally helped. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.26,0:06:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That helped me to organize \Nmy hours a little bit more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and also I’d get to know \Nmy brothers and sisters more as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the greatest joys of pioneering \Nhas been to pioneer with Mum. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.37,0:06:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had the privilege of going \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.94,0:06:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to the pioneer school together, \Nwhich was really special.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.64,0:06:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 16:8 reminds me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is right beside me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m preaching, \Nit’s like Jehovah is holding my hand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.95,0:06:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So with full-time service, \NI love making Jehovah happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,With everything that he has given me, \NI’m finally able to give something back.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking back\N—pioneering—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.66,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the best decision \NI’ve ever made. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s opened up \Nso many different avenues \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.53,0:06:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of service to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:06:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helped me also \Nto have that real desire \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.37,0:06:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to want to stay \Nin full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping someone \Non the road to everlasting life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s the best feeling ever; \Nand it’s really irreplaceable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.45,0:07:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I can say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.85,0:07:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“As a young person, start pioneering!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.39,0:07:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fine attitude \Nthose young ones have! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They are clearly following \Nin Jesus’ footsteps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was the wisest man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.03,0:07:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who ever walked the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.04,0:07:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He could’ve pursued any career \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.07,0:07:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and truly excelled at it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.08,0:07:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He could’ve been \Nthe greatest carpenter who ever lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.72,0:07:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,he helped his Father \Nbuild the physical universe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.62,0:07:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine \Nwhat kind of houses he could’ve built? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what if he had pursued \Nbeing an inventor? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.53,0:08:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With his perfect brain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,he probably could’ve invented \Nthe telephone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.94,0:08:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,automobile, or computer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.41,0:08:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what about becoming \Na businessman? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.54,0:08:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,With perfect intelligence, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.45,0:08:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he likely could’ve come out on top \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of every business transaction \Nthat he entered, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.89,0:08:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming the richest businessman \Nwho ever lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.72,0:08:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Or have you ever thought about \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if he had pursued becoming \Nan athlete? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.06,0:08:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And excelling in athletic contests \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.13,0:08:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was a huge endeavor in Jesus’ day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.80,0:08:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,With a little training, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it is likely that his perfect body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.74,0:08:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,would have outperformed all people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.41,0:08:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with imperfect bodies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.68,0:08:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,enabling him to become \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.15,0:08:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the most famous athlete who ever lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.96,0:09:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Or one more example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.22,0:09:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what if he had decided to become a doctor? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.46,0:09:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He could cure sick people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.43,0:09:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—even raise the dead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how much \Nhe could’ve charged rich people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to raise their dead loved ones? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus pursued none of these careers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he knew \Nthat any of such endeavors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,would have only very limited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and temporary benefits. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he pursued something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.19,0:09:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,he knew would bring far-reaching \Nand everlasting benefits: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.16,0:09:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the full-time ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.04,0:09:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is how the wisest man \Nwho ever walked the earth—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.14,0:09:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is how he reasoned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.41,0:09:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we are wise if we strive to think \Nthe same way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.35,0:10:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes me think of the comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of a well-adjusted teenage brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.25,0:10:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,whom we served \Nwhile in the circuit work many years ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.19,0:10:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This young brother went straight into \Nthe regular pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.86,0:10:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,out of high school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.86,0:10:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I asked him why he did so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.53,0:10:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He explained that he knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.20,0:10:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he could’ve gotten a full-time secular job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.64,0:10:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and bought a new car for himself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.38,0:10:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but he reasoned that in a few years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.25,0:10:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that car would rust out and break down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.79,0:10:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would have nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.02,0:10:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But he knew that he could go \Ninto the pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.09,0:10:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and build a close relationship \Nwith Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps even find \Nan honest-hearted person\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.03,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,, and be able to teach that one the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And he knew that would last forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:11:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that is some wise thinking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the part of that young brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.28,0:11:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, that brother \Nhas a beautiful Christian wife \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.75,0:11:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and several spiritual children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.22,0:11:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is serving as a fine elder.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.16,0:11:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you young ones \Nare going to think this way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and continue to pursue spiritual goals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.20,0:11:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it is vital that you wisely choose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.80,0:11:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,your associates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.11,0:11:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sense, our associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.68,0:11:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,can be likened to an elevator. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.11,0:11:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they can take you up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or they can take you down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.55,0:11:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose wisely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.82,0:11:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,they will take you up\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.12,0:11:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—elevate your good qualities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.83,0:11:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and make you a better person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you choose poorly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.33,0:11:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they will take you down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.10,0:12:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on how badly you choose, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.57,0:12:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they can take you way down\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—to the basement, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.04,0:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,even the subbasement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.35,0:12:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At Proverbs 13:20, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,our loving heavenly Father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.72,0:12:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,who made us, \Nexplains how it works. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.29,0:12:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah tells us there: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one walking with the wise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.49,0:12:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“will become wise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.26,0:12:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the one \Nwho has dealings with the stupid \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.50,0:12:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,will fare badly.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.81,0:12:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Walking with” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.81,0:12:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and “having dealings with” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.18,0:12:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,mean “associating with.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.61,0:12:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And who are the “stupid” ones? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.82,0:12:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this scripture contrasts \Nsuch a person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.45,0:12:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with those who are wise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.69,0:12:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not talking about someone \Nwho lacks mental intellect. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is talking about someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.06,0:13:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who does not make \Nwise decisions spiritually \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.93,0:13:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s standpoint. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.50,0:13:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone who is not really serving Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—at least right now—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.51,0:13:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is unwise indeed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.41,0:13:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we associate closely with such ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.45,0:13:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says that we “will fare badly.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use another illustration. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about someone who is physically sick \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.46,0:13:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and is running a high fever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.26,0:13:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If we spend a lot of time with that person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.93,0:13:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we will probably catch the same sickness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Or worse, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if we spend a lot of time \Nnear a dead body—a corpse—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.31,0:13:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we will probably pick up a disease. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.15,0:13:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it is similar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with spending time with a person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,who is spiritually sick, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or worse, spiritually dead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.69,0:14:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,if we choose as our associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,those who love Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and who are building \Ntheir everlasting future with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.67,0:14:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we will benefit greatly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.68,0:14:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please observe carefully \Nthis variety of young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.65,0:14:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,who are busy storing up \Ntreasures in heaven \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.99,0:14:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How heartwarming it is to us\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—and we know it is to Jehovah—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.78,0:16:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to see these beautiful young people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.05,0:16:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doing what Jesus encourages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.42,0:16:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 6:20, 21. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There, Jesus encourages: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.06,0:16:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Store up for yourselves \Ntreasures in heaven,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“where neither moth nor rust consumes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.37,0:17:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“and where thieves do not break in and steal.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.70,0:17:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“For where your treasure is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.47,0:17:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,there your heart will be also.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.81,0:17:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.98,0:17:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the final analysis, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.75,0:17:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,after all is said and done, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we are younger or older,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.65,0:17:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,, our net worth will be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.89,0:17:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what we have stored up \Nin heaven with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not be able to take \Nmaterial treasures with us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.63,0:17:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,through the great tribulation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.87,0:17:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we die, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.94,0:17:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we certainly will not be able to take \Nmaterial treasures with us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.17,0:17:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can take spiritual treasures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.31,0:17:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with us through the great tribulation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and even through death and resurrection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It is true with all of Jehovah’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is with the anointed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what is stated at Revelation 14:13. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:18:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It says there: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.46,0:18:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The things they did go right with them.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.27,0:18:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And how encouraging it is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.74,0:18:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to see young ones getting baptized\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.04,0:18:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—publicly demonstrating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.71,0:18:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are giving their lives to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.05,0:18:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we sincerely hope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.25,0:18:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that you young ones \Nwho are not yet baptized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.52,0:18:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,will not hold back from getting baptized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.82,0:18:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as you qualify. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The sooner you can get baptized, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.43,0:18:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the sooner you will receive \Ngreater protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and blessings from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long ago, \Nit made me very happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.24,0:18:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to observe a little ten-year-old brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,get baptized!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.15,0:18:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And young ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.18,0:18:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,never be afraid to identify yourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.02,0:19:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.19,0:19:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Never allow the fear \Nof what others may think \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.66,0:19:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to cause you to hesitate to do so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.73,0:19:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.73,0:19:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at Proverbs 29:25: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Trembling at men is a snare, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.45,0:19:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the one trusting in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.85,0:19:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will be protected.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago when I was in school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember being \Nat times somewhat worried \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.69,0:19:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about how my fellow classmates \Nwould view me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.36,0:19:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But then a little while later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.13,0:19:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I got out of school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.17,0:19:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and never ever again even saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.34,0:19:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,most of those former classmates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.27,0:19:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it dawned on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.18,0:19:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that it doesn’t really matter \Nwhat people think about us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.68,0:20:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Jehovah’s rating of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.52,0:20:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that truly counts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.92,0:20:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans cannot add \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.02,0:20:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,even five seconds to our lifespan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.36,0:20:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah can add \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.53,0:20:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or subtract eternity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.16,0:20:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And he alone \Ncan also give us true happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.70,0:20:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Proverbs 29:25 indicates, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what a protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.04,0:20:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it is to courageously identify ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.88,0:20:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.68,0:20:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,fully trusting Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and taking our stand solidly with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Never be ashamed of who you are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You are one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.84,0:20:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And please, dear young ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.37,0:20:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we warmly encourage you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to those who love you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves you very much; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.61,0:21:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body loves you very much; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.82,0:21:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders love you very much; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your Christian parents love you very much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.59,0:21:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And these ones will tell you the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.13,0:21:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,even though at times \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it may not be what you want to hear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.80,0:21:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They will not ‘tickle your ears,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps like ones at school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.94,0:21:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,or in the neighborhood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,who don’t really love you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.38,0:21:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or have your best interests at heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.71,0:21:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But please believe those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.68,0:21:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who will tell you the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.22,0:21:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because they love you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.59,0:21:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And never view \NJehovah’s laws and principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.29,0:21:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as depriving you of something good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.56,0:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,View them as protecting you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.13,0:22:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,from what will hurt you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.60,0:22:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you recall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan convinced Eve \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.27,0:22:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that she was being deprived by Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.58,0:22:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and was missing out on something good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.28,0:22:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it is true that Eve \Nwas missing out on something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.15,0:22:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But what was she really missing out on? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.29,0:22:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A tormented conscience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.26,0:22:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,her beautiful hair turning gray, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.09,0:22:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,her teeth falling out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.60,0:22:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,her perfect skin wrinkling up like a prune, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.40,0:22:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,being bent over from old age, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.31,0:22:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,hobbling around on a cane, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.31,0:22:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally dying! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.35,0:22:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But Satan convinced her \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.18,0:22:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was depriving her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.55,0:22:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so foolishly she reached out to get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.42,0:22:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what she thought she was missing out on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.96,0:23:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Satan will try to use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.90,0:23:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the same kind of strategy on you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.00,0:23:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but please don’t let him do it!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.44,0:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This also makes me think \Nof an experience a brother once related. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.98,0:23:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that he was visiting \Nan animal observatory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.12,0:23:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and a large lion lunged toward him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.05,0:23:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but was prevented from reaching him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,by a thick glass pane \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.49,0:23:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,separating the animals from the observers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.26,0:23:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As the lion stood on his hind legs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.40,0:23:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,clawing the glass \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and baring his massive teeth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.07,0:23:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the brother came to realize in a special way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.68,0:23:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the protective value of that barrier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.92,0:23:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously, he said \Nthat he somewhat viewed the glass pane \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.32,0:24:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as a restriction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.56,0:24:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because the smudges on it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.29,0:24:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,partially blurred his view, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.39,0:24:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he viewed it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.40,0:24:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as a real protection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.60,0:24:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in a similar way, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.60,0:24:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah doesn’t want Satan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.11,0:24:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who is described \Nas ‘a roaring, devouring lion’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.88,0:24:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Peter 5:8— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.88,0:24:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t want him \Nto gobble down you young ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.52,0:24:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And His laws and principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.22,0:24:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are designed to keep that \Nfrom happening to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.13,0:24:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So please listen to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.03,0:24:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He loves you!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.57,0:24:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You would probably agree \Nthat having good friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.27,0:24:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is of great encouragement \Nin your service to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.24,0:24:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You may also recognize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.58,0:25:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is more \Nto being a friend \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.12,0:25:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,than simply clicking links \Non a computer screen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.02,0:25:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or a smartphone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.72,0:25:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But where can you find \Ngood friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.06,0:25:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when there seems to be \Nno one to choose from? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.60,0:25:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.60,0:25:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,consider the example \Nof this young brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.77,0:25:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who struggled \Nwith this very question.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.11,0:25:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Akil. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.85,0:25:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 18, \Nmy family moved to a new city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.52,0:25:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was bad enough \Nleaving my friends behind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.96,0:25:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.52,0:25:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t sure \Nif I could make new ones.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.33,0:25:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents seemed really happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.74,0:25:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want \Nto make them feel bad \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.47,0:26:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by telling them how I really felt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.31,0:26:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The new school \Nwasn’t much better \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.85,0:26:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,until I met Cameron. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.92,0:26:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He seemed \Nlike a pretty cool guy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.10,0:26:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, his friends \Nbecame my friends.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.64,0:26:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . something that David \Nbelieved was true, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he actually proved it \Nby the association that he kept.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.41,0:26:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We think about one \Nof the closest friendships \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.45,0:26:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded in the Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.98,0:26:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was \Nthat of David and Jonathan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.52,0:26:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that David and Jonathan \Nshared in common? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.72,0:26:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t their age.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.19,0:26:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Akil, \Nyou were texting in the meeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.39,0:26:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn’t have sent the text. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.63,0:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.30,0:26:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But Cameron is a good person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.70,0:26:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He might even study one day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.27,0:27:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that, Akil. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.84,0:27:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But we all have to be careful \Nwith how much time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.81,0:27:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we spend with people \Nthat don’t love Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.31,0:27:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See, \Ntheir values are just different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.78,0:27:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know \Nwhat Proverbs 13:20 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.65,0:27:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Walk with those who are wise.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.68,0:27:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So why don’t you seek out \Nfriends who love Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.72,0:27:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will make friends \Nthat last a lifetime.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.62,0:27:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to do that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.12,0:27:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no one my age \Nin the congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.66,0:27:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Akil, good friends \Ncan come from unexpected places.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.43,0:27:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, \NI had good friends\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.10,0:27:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—back home.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.24,0:27:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We all felt bad that night.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.25,0:27:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.32,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Cameron posted pictures \Nof a party he had. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.52,0:27:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents were right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.86,0:28:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I broke off my association \Nwith Cameron \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.03,0:28:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and his friends, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.93,0:28:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but I still felt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.90,0:28:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,lost.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.94,0:28:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Akil? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.97,0:28:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have \Nfield service plans for Saturday?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.38,0:28:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.15,0:28:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. \NNow you do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.38,0:28:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll see you \Nat the 9:30 a.m. meeting, OK?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.50,0:28:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.97,0:28:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Max had the group \Nover for refreshments.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.71,0:28:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you take these?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.45,0:28:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you like them?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.55,0:28:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.68,0:28:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife, \Nshe was always the photographer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.22,0:28:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She loved photography. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.32,0:28:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one anniversary \Nshe went out and bought me a camera, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.89,0:29:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and from that moment on, \NI was hooked too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.33,0:29:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Time flies so quickly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.43,0:29:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s hard to believe \Nshe passed away 12 years ago now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.03,0:29:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.07,0:29:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s OK.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.54,0:29:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But you still take pictures?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.40,0:29:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I do. \NI really enjoy photography. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.17,0:29:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s something about being close \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.21,0:29:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah’s creation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.71,0:29:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.88,0:29:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’re never really alone, \Nyou know?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.02,0:29:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good friends can come \Nfrom unexpected places \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.36,0:29:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and unexpected ages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.86,0:29:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As I spent more time with Max, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.46,0:29:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized it was \Njust like David and Jonathan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.14,0:29:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their friendship was based, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.21,0:29:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not on age, \Nbut on their love for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.24,0:29:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And they helped each other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.55,0:30:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Max’s help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.19,0:30:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to keep \Na good spiritual routine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.79,0:30:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,without interruption. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.79,0:30:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we weren’t the same age, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.29,0:30:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Max became my good friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.30,0:30:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I just needed to see \Nwhat was right \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.50,0:30:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.61,0:30:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, friends can come in various ages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.61,0:30:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best kind of friend \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.48,0:30:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is one who encourages us\Nin our service to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.22,0:30:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We all need to work hard \Non making spiritual progress\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.82,0:30:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—learning new things \Nabout Jehovah and his qualities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.36,0:30:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want friends \Nwho will help us do that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.30,0:30:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a saying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.50,0:30:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience \Nis the best teacher, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.80,0:30:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is not \Nreally accurate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.31,0:31:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience is often \Nthe hard way to learn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.18,0:31:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Fernando Casillas \Nwas born in Mexico, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.95,0:31:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but when he was a baby, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.15,0:31:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,his family moved \Nto the United States. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The neighborhood he grew up in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.23,0:31:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,had a lot of gang influence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.33,0:31:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This had \Na very negative impact on him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.17,0:31:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite these circumstances, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.47,0:31:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how the truth attracted him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.18,0:31:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to love violence; \NI dreamed of violence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.81,0:31:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My gang was my religion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.78,0:31:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I got into the prison system \Nat a young age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.65,0:31:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, they sent me \Nto a juvenile facility, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.42,0:31:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but I got kicked out of there \Nfor a riot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.73,0:31:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, they deemed me a threat \Nto the safety and security \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.23,0:31:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of the institution, \Nthe guards, and other inmates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.40,0:32:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was sent \Nto solitary confinement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.60,0:32:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to finish off my prison term.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.64,0:32:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Me thinking \NI was violent back then \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.94,0:32:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was nothing compared to \Nwhat I came out with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.44,0:32:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically,\Nwhat you try to come out to be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.55,0:32:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best killer out of all.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.25,0:32:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,After my incarceration, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.02,0:32:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was deported to Mexico. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.56,0:32:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to carry a weapon \Nwith me everywhere I went.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.83,0:32:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, we started getting involved \Nwith bad people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.56,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, \Nmy girlfriend got in trouble. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.70,0:32:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Once that was over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.93,0:32:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,she saw a Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.94,0:32:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My girlfriend had been \Nto meetings as a child, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.94,0:32:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so she basically dragged me \Nto the Kingdom Hall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.71,0:32:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They treated me nice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.71,0:32:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s when I started \Nto get to know Omar. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.45,0:32:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started hanging around \Nwith him and his wife\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.95,0:32:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—me and my girlfriend at the time—\Nand going to meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.62,0:32:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t till I found out \Nthis guy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.62,0:32:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,used to be one of my rivals\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.76,0:32:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—I was very, very upset. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.89,0:32:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt betrayed because he never told me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.76,0:33:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that was going \Nthrough my head was, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.60,0:33:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ve got to find a way to get him over here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.60,0:33:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can hurt him.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.60,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After thinking about all the things \Nthat I wanted to do to him that night\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—I’d been running it through my head \Nover and over again—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.74,0:33:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to just stay friends with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.21,0:33:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually, \Nwe decided to start studying together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.21,0:33:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Being the way I was, \NI thought that there’s \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.28,0:33:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,no way a God can forgive me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.69,0:33:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture at Isaiah 55:7 \Nreally helped me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.09,0:33:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,where it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.36,0:33:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let the wicked man leave his way\Nand the evil man his thoughts; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.60,0:33:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,let him return to Jehovah, \Nwho will have mercy on him.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.20,0:33:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As time went by, \NI started understanding clearly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.00,0:33:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah does forgive.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.64,0:33:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, I had already \Nkind of made a decision\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.38,0:33:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was done\Nwith doing time in prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.41,0:33:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I just decided to cut all ties with everybody \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.95,0:33:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that had anything to do \Nwith anything illegal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.78,0:33:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like a free person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.78,0:33:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And after progressing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.62,0:34:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and quitting the habits that I had \Nof smoking and drinking a lot, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.06,0:34:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I became \Nan unbaptized publisher. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.96,0:34:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But my father passed away; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.20,0:34:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I started hanging around \Nwith bad association again, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.10,0:34:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually \NI had my privileges removed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.93,0:34:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And as that was happening, \NSatan attacked me again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.34,0:34:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So one day,\Nmy wife was crossing the border \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.57,0:34:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to go take care of\Nsome paperwork for the kids \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.21,0:34:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and was surprised\Nby the border patrol \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.78,0:34:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,telling her that there \Nwere drugs in the vehicle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.38,0:34:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not know \Nthat the previous owner \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.45,0:34:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,had stashed drugs in the truck. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.92,0:34:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though later they proved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.19,0:34:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that the drugs were not my wife’s\Nand she was released, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.89,0:34:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they still decided to keep my kids.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.06,0:34:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What I was thinking of doing \Nwas going back to my old ways\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.63,0:34:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—organizing a plot with my old friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.24,0:34:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring my kids\Nback to Mexico to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.04,0:34:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But I decided to rely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.07,0:34:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,on Jehovah instead \Nand on the brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.08,0:34:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,coming to visit me \Non a regular basis \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.01,0:34:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and giving me encouraging thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.71,0:35:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of how Jehovah \Nwill take care of everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.35,0:35:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, our kids were returned to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.55,0:35:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah’s help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.59,0:35:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After a little struggle, \Nof course, I had my privileges back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.76,0:35:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A few months later, I was baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.90,0:35:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a lot happier now \Nthan what I was back then. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.60,0:35:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One day as I was preaching\Nin the rehab centers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.47,0:35:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran into a person \NI once knew before, growing up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.17,0:35:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Once he found out who I was, he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.24,0:35:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’re the reason why I left town. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.95,0:35:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you would see me, \Nyou would shoot at me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.98,0:35:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So after a while, \NI was able to convince him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.18,0:35:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that actually my purpose there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was not to hurt him anymore \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.22,0:35:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but to teach him the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.06,0:35:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and how to gain everlasting life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.09,0:35:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m no longer a violent person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.26,0:35:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoy the privileges \Nthat Jehovah now gives me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.30,0:35:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have now been serving \Nas a ministerial servant \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.10,0:35:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for the past two years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.70,0:35:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m in charge of the accounting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.97,0:36:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Kingdom Hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.98,0:36:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of stealing money \Nas I used to do before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.05,0:36:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What I do for a living \Nis I do gardening work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.81,0:36:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I don’t carry around knives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.05,0:36:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but I carry around my tools. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.32,0:36:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say that I did beat \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.39,0:36:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,my pistols into plowshares now\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.72,0:36:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—or weed whacker or lawn mower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.33,0:36:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m glad that I’m \Nnow serving a great God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.23,0:36:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who is loving, \Ncaring, and forgiving.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.54,0:36:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fernando and his family\Nare serving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.14,0:36:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in an English congregation in Mexico. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.78,0:36:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,With everything \NBrother Casillas went through, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.32,0:36:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he could see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.35,0:36:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is the best teacher. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.49,0:36:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you listen to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.52,0:36:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you won’t have to learn \Nthe hard way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.90,0:36:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.90,0:37:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“the One teaching you \Nto benefit yourself.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.97,0:37:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 17:13 \Nconveys the thought \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.97,0:37:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that those \Nwho do not serve Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.38,0:37:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,will have their names \N“written in the dust.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.72,0:37:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But by building \Nyour future with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.29,0:37:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you young ones are ensuring \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.92,0:37:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah will keep\Nyour individual names\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.16,0:37:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,written in his “book of life” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.36,0:37:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that is mentioned \Nat Philippians 4:3 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.13,0:37:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and Revelation 3:5.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.20,0:37:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier in the program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.24,0:37:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw some examples \Nof how young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.71,0:37:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are building a future \Nwith Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.65,0:37:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what impact are such efforts \Nhaving on the organization? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.55,0:37:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at one example: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.72,0:37:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the construction \Nof the new world headquarters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.09,0:38:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at Warwick, New York.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.16,0:38:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses built \N1.6 million square feet (149,000 sq m) \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.57,0:38:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in less than four years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.67,0:38:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the 27,035 volunteers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.61,0:38:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,3,247 were between the ages of 19 and 25.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.01,0:38:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this was a project \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.15,0:38:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that was going to strictly need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.38,0:38:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,very experienced brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.09,0:38:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Early on, I realized I was wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.52,0:38:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was also going to take youthful energy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.69,0:38:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the volume of work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.20,0:38:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The mix of older and younger ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.20,0:38:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was really a helpful thing \Non the Warwick project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.70,0:38:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The older ones \Nbrought skill and experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.37,0:38:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The younger ones \Nbrought the energy, the muscle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.04,0:38:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the diligence to stay \Nwith hard physical tasks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.51,0:38:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way through the project.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.68,0:38:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it was in the kitchen\Nor night watch\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.62,0:38:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or the early 5:00 a.m. start \Nwith the concrete crew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.85,0:38:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,at 10 degrees Fahrenheit (-12°C), \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.99,0:39:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,their joy and their humility was outstanding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.65,0:39:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept any work that needed to be done.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.02,0:39:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And a lot of young ones, \Nbrothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.86,0:39:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,moved into the area \Nso they could commute.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.16,0:39:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would work \Nday after day tirelessly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.63,0:39:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,into the evenings even, \Nto have the project ready for the next day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.17,0:39:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Their energy was just astonishing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.27,0:39:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves young ones, \Nand he’s willing to invest in them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.81,0:39:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and train them and make them \Na part of his organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.61,0:39:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw that so much.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.08,0:39:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a lot of young people \Nwho offered themselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.09,0:39:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with technical skills. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.82,0:39:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the humility of these \Nvery technically-skilled young people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.53,0:39:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t match \Nor exceed their abilities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.03,0:39:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then, really, \NJehovah couldn’t use them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.03,0:39:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were willing to adjust, \Nand we really saw the benefit.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.70,0:39:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew and they knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.20,0:39:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were building \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.34,0:39:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not just a project at Warwick\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.11,0:39:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—they were building \Na spiritual project for Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.11,0:40:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You could see Jehovah’s spirit \Noperating on them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.01,0:40:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You could see them \Nmature so quickly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.45,0:40:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,These young brothers \Nare the next generation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.45,0:40:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of elders \Nand traveling overseers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.56,0:40:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re to be commended \Nand highly respected \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.56,0:40:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for the contribution \Nthey made as young men.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.93,0:40:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They all talk about the effect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.93,0:40:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that their Bethel service\Nhas had on their outlook\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.93,0:40:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they don’t want \Nto get caught up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.27,0:40:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world \Nand its daily pursuits.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.91,0:40:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the skills you’ve learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.64,0:40:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,here on this project and in Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.68,0:40:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You are needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.08,0:40:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue to keep your spirituality up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.18,0:40:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and to keep your association \Nat a high level.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.42,0:40:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest quality of life is when, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.99,0:40:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as clay, we put ourselves \Nin the hands of the Great Potter, Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.33,0:40:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and we say: \N“Here I am! Send me!”. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.33,0:40:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m fully confident \Nthey will have no regrets \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.07,0:41:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,building their future \Nwith Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.08,0:41:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, young ones \Ntruly had a beautiful impact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.82,0:41:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on the construction project \Nof world headquarters! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.55,0:41:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, \Nyou may find it interesting to know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.73,0:41:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Warwick \Nand Wallkill construction projects \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.73,0:41:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,were not funded\Nby the donations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.33,0:41:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have made \Nto the worldwide work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.57,0:41:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your donations are being used \Nto support the work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.71,0:41:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the worldwide field. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.38,0:41:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The massive construction projects \Nat Warwick and Wallkill \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.35,0:41:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,were funded by the sale \Nof properties in Brooklyn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.02,0:41:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, \Nwe just traded locations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.16,0:41:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We traded the value \Nof the properties in Brooklyn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.99,0:41:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the beautiful facilities \Nat Warwick and Wallkill. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.23,0:41:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I must say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.23,0:42:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body is truly enjoying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.30,0:42:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the new facility at Warwick, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.61,0:42:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to the hard work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.31,0:42:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,both of the young and the older ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.81,0:42:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who labored in our behalf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.98,0:42:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we truly appreciate it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.35,0:42:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul said of Timothy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.72,0:42:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded \Nat Philippians 2:20-23: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.80,0:42:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I have no one else \Nof a disposition like his \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.74,0:42:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“who will genuinely care \Nfor your concerns. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.77,0:42:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“For all the others \Nare seeking their own interests, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.98,0:42:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“not those of Jesus Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.78,0:42:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“But you know the proof \Nhe gave of himself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.02,0:42:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“that like a child with a father \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.02,0:42:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“he slaved with me \Nto advance the good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.46,0:43:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nhe is the one I am hoping to send.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.86,0:43:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It is obvious that Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.86,0:43:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,loved the young man Timothy very much \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.07,0:43:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his unselfish hard work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.27,0:43:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in behalf of Kingdom interests. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.34,0:43:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Governing Body \Nfeels exactly the same way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.31,0:43:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about you dear young ones \Nwho are working hard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.32,0:43:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in your various theocratic assignments.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.79,0:43:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to the many avenues \Nof full-time service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.33,0:43:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we mentioned earlier \Nin the program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.63,0:43:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,making yourself available \Nwhen a need arises locally \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.47,0:43:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is a fine way \Nto seek the Kingdom first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.34,0:43:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in San Antonio, \Nin the state of Texas, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.18,0:43:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.88,0:43:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a large convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.38,0:43:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with over 20,000 \Nin attendance was planned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.22,0:44:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Nthe venue could only provide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.49,0:44:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about one third of the chairs needed \Nfor the convention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.26,0:44:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would our brothers \Nfind the needed chairs? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.20,0:44:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah provided, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.07,0:44:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and many young ones \Nwere eager to help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.84,0:44:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard \Nthat this needed to happen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.15,0:44:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking, \N‘How are we going to do this?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.75,0:44:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, ‘It’s a big job!’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.25,0:44:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was amazing!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.79,0:44:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing I was asked to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.06,0:44:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was try to find a storage place \Nthat we could use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.62,0:44:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for six to eight thousand chairs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.33,0:44:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister manages a storage place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.96,0:44:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and we saw Jehovah’s blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.73,0:44:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because the owner said, \N“You can have this stall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.57,0:44:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“at no charge for a year \Nas long as you sign a contract \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.77,0:44:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that it’s \Nfor Jehovah’s Witnesses’ organization.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.77,0:44:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Truckload after truckload \Nafter truckload came in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.94,0:44:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to unload the trucks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.64,0:44:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers had \Nto unstack the chairs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.58,0:45:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,repair the chairs, clean the chairs, \Nput them back on pallets, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.28,0:45:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,restack them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.22,0:45:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,load them onto trucks, \Nand that was half of it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.75,0:45:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were the ones \Nin the warehouse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.76,0:45:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side, \Nwe got permission to ask \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.73,0:45:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the San Antonio congregations \Nif we could use their chairs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.03,0:45:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for the convention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.76,0:45:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We were hoping \Nto get three thousand chairs.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.00,0:45:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the numbers \Ngrew for the audience,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.07,0:45:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to increase \Nour numbers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.10,0:45:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were able to gather \Nsix thousand chairs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.64,0:45:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from the willing volunteers \Nof congregations around San Antonio.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.91,0:45:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we prayed about it and the brothers \Nstarted asking for volunteers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.78,0:45:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was a great cooperation \Nright at the beginning.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.52,0:45:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as \Nwe let the friends know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.89,0:45:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was going \Nto be the case, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.35,0:45:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all of them—\Nall of them said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.96,0:45:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“We’re going to get off \Nof work early.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.49,0:45:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We immediately wanted \Nto clear our schedules \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.93,0:45:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could be available \Nto help in any way that we could.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.93,0:45:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a privilege to know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.10,0:45:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that our congregation \Nwas going to be part of it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.77,0:45:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We are so grateful to Jehovah \Nthat he has given us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.07,0:46:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this privilege to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.07,0:46:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We had thousands of chairs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.81,0:46:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of every color\N—green, red, brown, blue. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.48,0:46:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We even had some bright orange ones \Nleft out of the ‘70’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.85,0:46:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re putting those in the back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.65,0:46:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was not just the colors \Nbut the sizes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.35,0:46:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all different sizes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.39,0:46:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so how do you make \Nsections with straight rows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.59,0:46:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when the chairs \Nare all different sizes?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.76,0:46:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But I knew somehow, \Nas Jehovah’s people, we’d get it done. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.93,0:46:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we definitely— \NAs you see, a lot of volunteers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.30,0:46:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re here getting it done.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.94,0:46:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s made \Nfor a beautiful experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.50,0:46:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because the friends have gotten to know \Neach other as never before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.91,0:46:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And they’re willingly \Nworking together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.84,0:46:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the excitement is there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.64,0:46:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t matter whose venue it is, \Nit’s all for Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.55,0:46:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s been \Nthe attitude everybody has had.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.72,0:46:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It just tells you \Nthat Jehovah is a God of order.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.82,0:46:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good to feel \Nthat you’re doing your best for Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.92,0:46:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it reminds me of Psalm 127:1,\Nwhere it mentions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.39,0:46:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘unless Jehovah builds the house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.23,0:46:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s in vain that his workers \Neven work hard.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.87,0:47:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s because of Jehovah’s hand \Nand his blessing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.37,0:47:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is why everything \Nruns so smoothly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.37,0:47:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What other organization! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.84,0:47:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else can do that \Nexcept Jehovah’s people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.01,0:47:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It truly is a fine witness \Nwhen our young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.88,0:47:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,wholeheartedly give \Nof their time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.05,0:47:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 20:29 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.29,0:47:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“The glory of young men \Nis their strength.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.06,0:47:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And commendably, \Nyou young men and women \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.63,0:47:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are using your strength \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.24,0:47:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a name \Nwith Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.67,0:47:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever considered \Nhelping out in a foreign-language field? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.15,0:47:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps there is a need \Nin your local circuit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.15,0:47:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All over the earth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.35,0:47:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the organization \Nprovides language courses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.29,0:48:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the goal of reaching \Nevery nation, tribe, tongue, and people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.19,0:48:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with the good news of God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.96,0:48:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Juan Carlos Chacón \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.63,0:48:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,serves as a special pioneer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.80,0:48:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the rapidly growing Shuar language field\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.07,0:48:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in Ecuador.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.58,0:48:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was recently asked to attend\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.08,0:48:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a course at the local branch \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.82,0:48:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a language teacher \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.82,0:48:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he could help \Nwilling publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.52,0:48:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,learn the language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.93,0:48:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[Speaking Shuar]\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.14,0:48:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been said before, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.04,0:48:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is a language of the Devil”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.14,0:48:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—that it should be forgotten. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.55,0:48:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It serves no purpose. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.35,0:49:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.52,0:49:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,no nation is insignificant.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.33,0:49:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up in an area \Nof the Ecuadorian jungle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.87,0:49:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,where there is \Na large community \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.87,0:49:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of Shuar people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.67,0:49:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Like many native languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.71,0:49:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuar is very complex. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.42,0:49:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We need many, many workers in the field. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.92,0:49:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we don’t give them a foundation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.19,0:49:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,if we don’t help them \Nor give them a little push, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.72,0:49:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s difficult for them to enter this field.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.73,0:49:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I received an invitation to attend \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.70,0:49:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a seminar for language instructors. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.04,0:49:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There were 58 students in the class, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.54,0:50:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,representing 16 different languages \Nor language groups.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.49,0:50:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We are learning \Nfantastic teaching techniques, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.93,0:50:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,real techniques that work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.77,0:50:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The instructor told us how humor helps \Nour minds to create a world of connections, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.91,0:50:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which stimulates our brain.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.38,0:50:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I’m like a small child \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.05,0:50:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to drawing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.09,0:50:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I never learned to draw well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.69,0:50:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We draw a scene, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.73,0:50:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and starting with our native language \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.90,0:50:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,along with large gestures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.83,0:50:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we act out a dialogue.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.27,0:50:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Little by little,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.27,0:50:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we convert the scene\Ninto the new language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.93,0:51:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What scares me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.93,0:51:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That I’ve never done this before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.00,0:51:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be my first time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.44,0:51:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have any experience \Nteaching languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.22,0:51:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I felt intimidated by this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.15,0:51:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that with Jehovah \Nall things are possible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.53,0:52:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the first day \Nof the Shuar language course.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.58,0:52:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The techniques they offered us \Nin the course were like a box of tools \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.49,0:52:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that we need to study more carefully \Nand see how to apply them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.09,0:52:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in each circumstance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.73,0:52:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When we are in the territory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.73,0:52:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we see how people’s eyes \Nlight up when they learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.17,0:52:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.17,0:52:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just seeing that there is so much need \Nfor them to learn the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.11,0:52:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that has motivated us to come here \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.48,0:52:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and continue serving here.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.26,0:52:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Since God has created us,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.26,0:52:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that he will\Nnever abandon us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.73,0:53:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks about us all the time,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.73,0:53:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and he loves us very much.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.90,0:53:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know that before.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.93,0:53:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel so happy now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.70,0:53:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I can really understand \Nthe Word of God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.57,0:53:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Being in an isolated group\Nfar from other congregations,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.75,0:53:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,my wife and I \Nhave felt every day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.98,0:53:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,how real Jehovah is.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.72,0:53:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is now looking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.72,0:53:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and giving his attention \Nto these small places, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.99,0:53:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how small they are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.52,0:53:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If people have a good heart \Nand want to serve Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.00,0:53:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he will send workers\Nto give the help that is needed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.57,0:53:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And in reality, this moves us \Nto say to him with all of our heart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.97,0:53:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Thank you, Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.12,0:53:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a lot to do \Nin Jehovah’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.49,0:54:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of our age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.49,0:54:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if our circumstances \Nmay restrict us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.73,0:54:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sees and values \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.26,0:54:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,all of our efforts \Nto expand our ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.94,0:54:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to build \Nan everlasting future with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.44,0:54:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our music video for this month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.44,0:54:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is appropriately entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.68,0:54:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Building My Future With Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.46,0:54:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, I wish I could see \Nexactly what my future will be\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.84,0:54:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And how my life will turn out \Nand which road is the right one for me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.65,0:55:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But one thing’s for sure, \Nno matter what comes along,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.85,0:55:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I live for Jehovah, \Nto him I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.69,0:55:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the people and things \Nmy life could be filled with,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.07,0:55:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The best one of all, \Nthe best one to build with,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.74,0:55:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is pleasing Jehovah each day \Nwith the choices I make.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.51,0:55:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me all that I have; \NI’ll never forget it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.72,0:55:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m safe in his hands; \NI’ll never regret it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.09,0:55:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m building my future with him \Nev’ry step that I take.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.96,0:55:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, the chance comes along \Nto take a path I know to be wrong,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.87,0:56:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A path that leads me away \Nfrom the place that I know I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.31,0:56:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But keeping in mind \Nthe dedication I made\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.16,0:56:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Can give me the firmness and faith \Nthat won’t fade.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.13,0:56:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the people and things \Nmy life could be filled with,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.90,0:56:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The best one of all, \Nthe best one to build with,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.11,0:56:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Is pleasing Jehovah each day \Nwith the choices I make.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.45,0:56:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me all that I have; \NI’ll never forget it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.59,0:56:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m safe in his hands; \NI’ll never regret it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.93,0:56:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m building my future with him \Nev’ry step that I take.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.87,0:57:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m building a future \Nthat never will end\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.70,0:57:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I build it with help \Nfrom Jehovah, my Friend.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.28,0:57:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The happiest moments, \Nthe best life can give,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.38,0:57:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Come from pleasing Jehovah \Neach day that I live.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.34,0:57:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the people and things \Nmy life could be filled with,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.01,0:57:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The best one of all, \Nthe best one to build with,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.65,0:57:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is pleasing Jehovah each day \Nwith the choices I make.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.72,0:58:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me all that I have; \NI’ll never forget it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.59,0:58:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m safe in his hands; \NI’ll never regret it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.33,0:58:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m building my future with him \Nev’ry step that I take.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.01,0:58:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m building my future \Nwith him ev’ry step that I take.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.19,0:58:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,An encouraging song indeed! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.53,0:58:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage all young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.53,0:58:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the message of this program\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.87,0:58:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—to build a future with Jehovah—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.57,0:58:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.57,0:58:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayerfully consider what you can do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.51,0:58:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand your ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.68,0:58:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Always safeguard \Nyour most valuable possession\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.72,0:59:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—your precious relationship \Nwith Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.42,0:59:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Never forget \Nthat there are more with you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.86,0:59:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than there are against you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.63,0:59:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It is true that Satan, the demons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.07,0:59:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and this world are against you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.07,0:59:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But your brothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.84,0:59:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,including the Governing Body, \Nare with you; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.41,0:59:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the angels are with you; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.28,0:59:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the resurrected immortal anointed ones \Nare with you; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.09,0:59:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is with you; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.59,0:59:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and most important, \NJehovah is with you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.19,0:59:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You are never alone!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.83,0:59:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.84,0:59:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we have greetings \Nto share with you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.17,0:59:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from the special convention \Nthat was held \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.84,0:59:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in July of last year\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.61,0:59:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in Paris, France.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.75,1:00:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the privilege \Nof attending this convention \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.55,1:00:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with Brother Kenneth Flodin,\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.58,1:00:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Teaching Committee.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.59,1:00:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,While most of the convention program \Nwas in French, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.59,1:00:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it was simultaneously interpreted \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.89,1:00:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,into Croatian, English, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.13,1:00:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and Polish \Nfor the benefit \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.66,1:00:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the international delegates.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.07,1:00:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be happy to know \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.07,1:00:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that 71 new sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.44,1:00:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and 41 new brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.91,1:00:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,symbolized their dedication \Nthrough water baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.65,1:00:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The oldest baptismal candidate \Nwas an 80-year-old sister \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.98,1:00:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the youngest \Nwas a 10-year-old.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.39,1:00:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The young candidates \Nhad to overcome \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.39,1:00:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,various challenges in order \Nto reach their goal \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.39,1:00:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.39,1:00:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Four of them took this step \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.39,1:00:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,even though their parents \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.43,1:00:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,are not Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.43,1:00:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of these dear young ones \Nhad to overcome \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.87,1:00:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,peer pressure at school\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.87,1:00:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—pressure to do things \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.44,1:01:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does not like. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.44,1:01:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of the young brothers, \Nalso fleshly brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.51,1:01:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,used to play \Nviolent video games. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.61,1:01:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Through their personal Bible study \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.78,1:01:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and the personal interest \Nshown in them, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.15,1:01:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they came to understand \NJehovah’s viewpoint on violence \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.16,1:01:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and made the necessary changes \Nto progress spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.86,1:01:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By taking this first step \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.86,1:01:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting baptized, \Nthese brothers and sisters have shown\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.20,1:01:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that they want to build a future \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.57,1:01:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.60,1:01:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us all do everything \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.17,1:01:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we can to continue making \Nspiritual progress, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.41,1:01:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which will bring \NJehovah’s smile of approval. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.78,1:01:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters, \Nwe love you very much. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.49,1:01:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.69,1:01:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.35,0:00:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ようこそいらっしゃいました！\N今月の新しいJW Broadcastingです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.33,0:00:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回は 王国を第一にしている \N世界中の若い人たちに注目しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:27.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 若い時にいろいろな問題を\N経験した 一人の兄弟をご紹介します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.58,0:00:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうやって 真理の助けで生き方を\N変えたでしょうか？楽しみですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:40.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして エクアドルの言語訓練コース\Nの様子も見ましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:46.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい言語を学んで宣教を拡大するとは\Nいったいどういうものでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.10,0:00:48.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,探ってみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.10,0:00:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでは 3月のJW Broadcating\Nスタートです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.66,0:01:16.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のブロードキャストの主題は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.96,0:01:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“若い皆さん エホバと共に\N 将来を築きましょう！”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.67,0:01:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら\Nテモテ第一 6章19節にある通り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.04,0:01:34.34,Default2,,0,0,0,, “自分のため 将来に対する\N りっぱな土台を安全に蓄え—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.34,0:01:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,, “真の命をしっかりとらえる”ことに\N なるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:44.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん わたしたちはこの話を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:51.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織にいる愛する若い皆さんに\N直接語りかけたいと思っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.19,0:01:53.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 考えてみると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:57.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが生きたいと願っている\N永遠という時間と比べると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.73,0:02:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは皆\N比喩的に言って若者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:05.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから ある意味で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.34,0:02:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このブロードキャストで話されることは\Nわたしたち皆に当てはまります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:15.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,高校卒業後すぐに\N開拓奉仕をするようにとの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.85,0:02:18.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,積極的な仲間の圧力があったことを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.86,0:02:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは個人的に\Nエホバに感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.29,0:02:28.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはわたしにとって祝福であり\N保護になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.90,0:02:32.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,17歳で正規開拓奉仕を始め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.14,0:02:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,18歳でベテルに行くことが\Nできたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.78,0:02:41.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,大学教育を追い求めるようにとの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,周囲からのかなりの圧力が\Nありましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.82,0:02:47.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの助けのおかげで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.85,0:02:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に将来を築くという決定が\Nできたのは大きな喜びです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.93,0:02:59.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは何も後悔していません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心からエホバに仕えている若者たちも\N同様に感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.07,0:03:10.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,後悔などはしていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.41,0:03:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでは エホバと共に将来を築いている\N若者たちの声をお聞きください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.12,0:03:28.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓を始める前は 毎月 \N時間が入るか不安でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:32.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,車がなかったから \N始めるのはちょっと大変でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:35.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,上司はパートを\N認めてくれませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:39.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校と開拓の両立は大変でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:42.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,一番の障害は人への恐れでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:45.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,人と話すのが苦手だったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.48,0:03:48.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い習慣を持つのに苦労しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.95,0:03:52.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理にいるのは兄とわたしだけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.15,0:03:57.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんで奉仕に行きたいのか\N家族に理解してもらえませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.02,0:03:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,できるとは思えませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.49,0:04:03.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,5歳の時からⅠ型の糖尿病なので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.43,0:04:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,健康と開拓のバランスが取れるか \Nいつも心配でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.40,0:04:13.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,今と比べて以前は \Nもっと問題が大きかったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.90,0:04:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの助けが すご過ぎです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.04,0:04:20.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈って恐れを克服しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.11,0:04:23.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族はエホバからの強力な助けです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.38,0:04:27.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓を最初に励ましてくれたのは父です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:31.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族からのフルサポートを\N約束してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.89,0:04:35.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,若いときに全時間奉仕をした\N兄弟姉妹と話すことが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.53,0:04:37.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな助けになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:39.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごく力をもらって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしも全時間奉仕を経験したい\Nっていう気持ちになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:47.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,できることをしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.44,0:04:51.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,車がないから 歩くかバスに乗りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:53.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,優先順位を決めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:57.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎週 何時間奉仕すべきか考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:05:02.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから 曜日ごとに いつ奉仕して \Nいつ学校に行くか計画を立てました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.75,0:05:06.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,宿題とか研究する時間も\N取れるようにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.92,0:05:08.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,予定を立ててよかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.93,0:05:11.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,やることを全部書きだしてみたら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.13,0:05:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,要求時間を達成できるって分かって\N無理って思わなくなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めは 特別活動の月に\N開拓をする短期的な目標を持ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:26.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから 連続で補助をして \N最終的に正規開拓を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:30.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごくよかった開拓の準備は \N補助開拓です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.85,0:05:33.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓をしながら\N直面するどんな困難も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.88,0:05:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,克服できるよう準備できました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.92,0:05:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラキ 3章10節を考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.42,0:05:44.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼していたけど \N試みるいい機会でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈って エホバを信頼し \N申し込みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.17,0:05:55.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者になってしばらくして \Nある兄弟が仕事をくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.34,0:05:58.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,3か月仕事がなかったから大変でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.94,0:06:03.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも その間に \Nエホバに注意を集中しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.31,0:06:08.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは支えてくださって \N見捨てたりされませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.32,0:06:10.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕する人が少ない日に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:13.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹に一緒に働くよう\Nお願いしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:15.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごく助けになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.59,0:06:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,もっと時間を活用できるし \N兄弟姉妹をよく知ることもできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.16,0:06:25.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごく嬉しいのは\N母と開拓ができることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ開拓者学校に行けて\Nとてもよかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.67,0:06:36.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 16編8節からエホバが\Nすぐそばにいてくださると分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:40.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕のとき \N手を握ってくださっているみたいです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.45,0:06:43.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,全時間奉仕をして \Nエホバを喜ばせたいです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.99,0:06:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,与えられたものすべてを用いて \Nやっと少しお返しできます \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.46,0:06:52.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,振り返れば \N開拓は今までで最善の決定です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへのいろんな\N奉仕の道が開かれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 全時間奉仕を続ける\N真の願いを持つ助けにもなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.74,0:07:04.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,道行く人を永遠の命へ導くのは \N最高です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何にも代えられません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.81,0:07:11.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,勧めたいことはただ1つ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.98,0:07:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“若いうちに 開拓奉仕！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.59,0:07:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何と立派な態度ではないでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この若者たちは\Nイエスのあとに従っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは地上で最も賢い人でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.07,0:07:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな職業にも優れた能力を\N発揮できたでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で最高の大工になれたはずです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.25,0:07:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは父を助けて\N物質の宇宙を造りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.25,0:07:55.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな家を建てることができたか\N想像できますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:08:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,発明家になっていたら\Nどうでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,完全な頭脳を使って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.13,0:08:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,電話や車やコンピューターを\N西暦1世紀に発明できたことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.97,0:08:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビジネスマンになっていたら\Nどうでしょう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.78,0:08:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,完璧な知性を使って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.02,0:08:23.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分がかかわった\Nあらゆる商業取引から利益を上げ— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界一の大富豪になることが\Nできたでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.89,0:08:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは運動選手になっていたら\Nどうだったか考えたことがありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの時代 運動競技で勝つためには\N大きな努力が求められました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.34,0:08:48.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,完全な体を持つイエスは\Nほんのわずかな訓練で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:49.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,不完全な体を持つ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:53.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,他のすべての選手よりも\N優れたパフォーマンスをして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で最も優れた運動選手に\Nなったことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.62,0:09:01.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一つの例です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.76,0:09:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが医者になっていたら\Nどうでしょう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:07.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気の人を癒し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,死者を生き返らせることも\Nできたでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.34,0:09:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人を生き返らせるとどれくらいの料金を\Nお金持ちから請求できたと思いますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:22.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも イエスは\Nこのいずれをも追い求めませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.31,0:09:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:28.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは イエスがこのいずれもが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.52,0:09:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に限られた一時的な益しか\Nもたらさないことを知っていたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:40.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,代わりに イエスはより多くの人に\N永続的な益をもたらすもの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.50,0:09:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり全時間宣教を追い求めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.17,0:09:50.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,地上で最も賢い人が推論して\Nそう結論したのであれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.81,0:09:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも同じように考えて\N賢い者であることを示せるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.25,0:10:01.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前 巡回奉仕をしていた時に会った—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.72,0:10:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,良く訓練された十代の兄弟の\N語ったことを思い出しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:14.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,この若い兄弟は 高校卒業後すぐに\N正規開拓奉仕を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはなぜそうしたのか\N聞いてみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:26.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟が言うには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.21,0:10:31.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,全時間の仕事について\N自分で新車を買うこともできるけれど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.05,0:10:34.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,数年もたてば車はさびてダメになるし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.08,0:10:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしたら何も残らなくなるって\N考えたそうです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:46.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 兄弟は開拓奉仕を始めて\Nエホバとの近しい関係を築き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:48.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の正直な人々を見つけて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を教えることができるかもしれない\Nことを知っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.47,0:10:58.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして それが永続する益をもたらす\Nことを知っていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.87,0:11:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この若い兄弟がそう考えたのは\N賢明なことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.38,0:11:06.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,この兄弟には\N美しいクリスチャンの妻と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.88,0:11:09.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾人かの霊的な子どもたちがおり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いま兄弟は立派な長老として\N奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:23.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも若い皆さん このように考え\N霊的な目標を追い求めたいなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.63,0:11:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の友を賢く選ぶことは大切です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:36.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある意味 友はエレベーターに\N例えることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.61,0:11:38.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういう意味でしょう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.71,0:11:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたを引き上げたり\N引き降ろしたりするということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.29,0:11:48.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢明に選ぶなら\N引き上げてくれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.46,0:11:53.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い特質を伸ばし\Nより良い人にならせてくれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.66,0:11:58.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも まずい選択をすると\N引き降ろされるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:01.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,選択がどれほどまずいかによって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.97,0:12:04.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,地下室まで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.71,0:12:06.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,場合によっては—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.11,0:12:10.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,地下2階にまで\N引きずり降ろされてしまいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.15,0:12:12.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言13章20節で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.28,0:12:18.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちを造られた愛ある天の父は \Nその点をこう説明されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.65,0:12:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこう述べておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:28.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,“賢い者たちと共に歩んでいる者は\N 賢くなり—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.56,0:12:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“愚鈍な者たちと交渉を持つ者は\N 苦しい目に遭う”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.71,0:12:42.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,“共に歩む”とか“交渉を持つ”とは\N“友になる”と言う意味です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.98,0:12:46.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,では“愚鈍な者”とはだれですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖句はそのような人を\N賢い人と対比しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.39,0:12:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは勉強ができない人のことでは\Nありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:12:58.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはエホバの基準からして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:13:03.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に賢い決定をしない人のことを\N述べているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:05.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう考えると— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.03,0:13:09.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,少なくとも 今のこの時に\Nエホバに仕えようとしていない人は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.27,0:13:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれであれ 全く賢い人ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.61,0:13:19.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてそのような人たちと\Nいつも一緒にいるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.55,0:13:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは“苦しい目に遭う”と\N述べておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の例えを考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気にかかっていて\N高熱のある人がいるとします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.33,0:13:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人と長い時間共に過ごすなら\N同じ病気にかかってしまうことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:45.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,もっと悪いことに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.74,0:13:49.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,死んだ人つまり死体のそばに\N長時間いるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.98,0:13:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気に感染することでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:59.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に病気の人 さらに悪いことに\N霊的に死んでいる人と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間を過ごすことについても\N同じことが言えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:12.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,一方 エホバを愛し エホバと共に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.40,0:14:16.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の将来を築こうとしている人々を\N友として選ぶなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは\N大いに益を受けることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.91,0:14:26.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に忙しく\N天に宝を蓄えている—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.28,0:14:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の様々な若者たちのことを\Nどうぞ注意深くご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.60,0:16:31.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらのりっぱな若者たちが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.11,0:16:34.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの次の勧めを\N実践しているのを見るのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.28,0:16:37.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちにとって\N心温まるものですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.08,0:16:40.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはエホバにとってもそうでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.58,0:16:45.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはマタイ 6章20, 21節\Nの言葉です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはこう言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.39,0:16:51.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自分のために天に宝を蓄えなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:54.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そこでは蛾もさびも食わず”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:58.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,“盗人が押し入って\N 盗むこともありません”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.93,0:17:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの宝のある所\N そこにあなたの心もあるのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:13.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,色々考えてきましたが\N結局のところ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.12,0:17:16.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,老若を問わず わたしたちの真価は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に何を天に蓄えたか\Nということになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.96,0:17:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,物質の宝を持って\N大患難を通過することはできません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.23,0:17:37.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,死んでしまうなら\N物質の宝を持って行くことなどできません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.24,0:17:41.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 霊的な宝は\N大患難を通過するときも\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.94,0:17:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,死と復活を経験したとしても\N携えて行くことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.19,0:17:52.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,啓示 14章13節は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:57.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,油そそがれた者についても\Nすべてのエホバの民にも当てはまります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.39,0:18:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこには “彼らの行なったことは\Nそのまま彼らに伴って行く”とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.30,0:18:13.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さんがバプテスマを受けるのを\N見ると 本当に大きな励みになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.41,0:18:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは自分の命をエホバにささげたことを\N公に示すことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.75,0:18:25.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだバプテスマを受けていない\N若い皆さんが資格をとらえたならすぐ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.19,0:18:27.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けることを\Nちゅうちょしないように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心からお勧めしたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:35.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを早く受ければ\Nそれだけ早く—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバからの大きな保護と祝福を\N受けることができるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.17,0:18:44.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,それほど昔のことではありませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,10歳のかわいい兄弟がバプテスマを\N受けたのを見てとてもうれしく思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:56.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さん\N自分がエホバの証人であることを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.95,0:19:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,明らかにすることを\N決して恐れないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.66,0:19:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの人がどう思うかと恐れて\N自分のことを隠してはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.40,0:19:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは箴言 29章25節で\Nこう述べておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.77,0:19:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“人に対するおののきは わなとなる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.07,0:19:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし エホバに依り頼んでいる者は\N 保護される“\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.92,0:19:31.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと昔 学校にいたころのことですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:34.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,時々クラスメイトは自分のことを\Nどう思っているのだろうかと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.79,0:19:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安な気持ちになったことがありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.60,0:19:44.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも それから少したって\N卒業しましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは以前のクラスメートのほとんどに\N一度も会ったことがありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.77,0:19:52.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで気づいたのですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.84,0:19:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人が自分の事をどう思うかは\N本当は重要ではないのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.48,0:20:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがどう思われるかが重要なのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.62,0:20:09.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間は寿命を5秒たりとも\N延ばすことはできませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは永遠を人に与えたり\N取り去ったりできるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバだけが\N真の幸福を与えることができる方です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:27.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言 29章25節が\N示しているように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.84,0:20:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気をもって自分がエホバの証人で\Nあることを明らかにし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.05,0:20:37.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを全く信頼して\Nエホバにしっかり付くなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはわたしたちにとって\N素晴らしい保護となります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.66,0:20:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分がだれであるかを\N決して恥じてはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.46,0:20:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたはエホバの証人なのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.44,0:20:57.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛する若い皆さん\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.37,0:21:02.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを愛している人たちの\N言うことを聞いてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.81,0:21:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ神は皆さんを愛しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:09.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体も皆さんを愛しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.48,0:21:12.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,長老たちもそうです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:15.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,クリスチャンの親たちもそうです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.96,0:21:19.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの人たちは\Nあなたに真理を語ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.83,0:21:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが聞きたくないと\N思うようなことも語ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.73,0:21:26.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの人たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.47,0:21:30.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの“耳をくすぐる”ようなことは\N言いません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:33.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当はあなたを愛しておらず\Nあなたの最善を願っていない—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.51,0:21:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校の友達や近所の人たちとは\N違うのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:41.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも あなたを愛しているからこそ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.58,0:21:46.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたに真理を語る\Nこれらの人たちを信じてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.86,0:21:49.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして エホバの律法や原則のために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.12,0:21:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か良いものを得損なっている\Nとは決して思わないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.06,0:22:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはあなたを傷つけるものから\Nあなたを守っているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.54,0:22:04.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い出してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:06.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンは\Nエホバが制限を設けているために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.74,0:22:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か良いものを得損なっていると\Nエバに思い込ませました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.91,0:22:16.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エバが何かを得損なっていたのは\N本当です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.75,0:22:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも実際には\N何を得損なっていたでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.29,0:22:23.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,良心の呵責に苦しむこと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.49,0:22:26.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,美しい髪が白髪になること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.70,0:22:29.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,歯が抜け落ちること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.77,0:22:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,もち肌に深いしわが生じること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.34,0:22:37.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,年と共に腰が曲がること— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:40.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,杖をついてよぼよぼになること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.64,0:22:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に死を迎えることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.25,0:22:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンはエホバが何かを奪っていると\Nエバに思い込ませました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.12,0:22:53.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,愚かにも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.49,0:22:59.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,エバはいわば自分が得損なっていると\N思ったものを得るようになったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.90,0:23:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンはあなたにも同様の策略を\N用いようとするでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.87,0:23:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも決してそうさせてはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.24,0:23:17.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,先ほどお話しした兄弟の経験を\N思い起こします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.01,0:23:21.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟によると\Nある動物観察施設に行った時のこと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.35,0:23:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きなライオンが\N兄弟に向かって突進してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.39,0:23:30.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 動物とその施設を隔てていた\N分厚いガラスのおかげで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンは来ることができませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.87,0:23:40.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンは後ろ脚で立ちあがり\N爪でガラスをひっかき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.67,0:23:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな牙をむき出していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.81,0:23:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟はその保護バリアのありがたさを\N特別な仕方で実感しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.62,0:23:59.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟によると ガラスに汚れが\Nついていると良く見えないので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.79,0:24:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それまでは そのガラスの塀は\N余計なものと見ていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.36,0:24:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 今では本当に保護するものだと\Nみなすようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.17,0:24:15.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,同様にサタンは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.67,0:24:18.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロ第一 5章8節で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.81,0:24:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ほえて歩き回る”ライオン\N として描かれています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.55,0:24:27.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでエホバは若い人たちがサタンに\Nむさぼり食われるようなことを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.92,0:24:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,願ってはおられません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.52,0:24:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの律法と原則は\N皆さんを守るためのものなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.29,0:24:41.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうか エホバの言われることを\N聞いてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.06,0:24:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはあなたを愛しておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.93,0:24:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い友と一緒にいると \N勇気がわいてくると思いませんか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.31,0:24:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのために奉仕し続けよう \Nという気持ちになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.34,0:24:58.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも気づいていると思いますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.88,0:25:02.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い友を見つけて友情を育てたいなら— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.48,0:25:05.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,パソコンとかスマホのSNSとかを\N使って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.69,0:25:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,知り合えばよい というわけ\Nではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.66,0:25:14.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 良い友がなかなか見つからない—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.33,0:25:18.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう感じるとき \Nどうしたらよいでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.13,0:25:20.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のドラマを見ましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.70,0:25:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことを考えている \N若い兄弟が登場します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.44,0:25:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,名前はアキル\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.18,0:25:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,18の時 家族で引っ越した\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.02,0:25:41.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,友達と別れるのは辛かった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.52,0:25:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに 新しくできるかも分からない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:53.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,両親はとても幸せそう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.47,0:25:56.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから心配をかけたくない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.57,0:26:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕の気持ちを話すと\Nがっかりするだろうから\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.85,0:26:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校は退屈だった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.25,0:26:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,キャメロンに会うまでは\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.06,0:26:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いい奴そうだな\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.66,0:26:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに 友達が増えた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.60,0:26:32.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,…ダビデの信頼は心からのもので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.24,0:26:35.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼が保った友情がそれを証ししています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.88,0:26:38.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデとヨナタンの友情関係について—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.18,0:26:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書から考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.58,0:26:46.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人の友情は何に基づいていましたか？\N年齢でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.59,0:26:49.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,アキル 集会中メールしてたわね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.72,0:26:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かってる ごめん\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.23,0:26:57.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも キャメロンはいい奴なんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.13,0:26:59.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつか研究するかも\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.60,0:27:01.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,気持ちは分かるよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.37,0:27:07.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバを愛さない人と\Nいつも一緒にいることには注意しないと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.28,0:27:09.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,持ってる基準が違うね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.44,0:27:14.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言 13章20節が言うように\N“賢い者たちと共に歩”むんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.45,0:27:17.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛する友達を探してごらん\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.62,0:27:19.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと続く友達が見つかるよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.99,0:27:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうやってできるの？\N会衆に同い年なんていないよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.16,0:27:27.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,親友は思いがけないところにいるものよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.66,0:27:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,親友は…いたよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.57,0:27:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,前にね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.41,0:27:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その夜はたくさん話し合った\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.15,0:27:55.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の日 キャメロンが\Nパーティーの写真を見せてくれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.96,0:27:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,両親は正しかった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.33,0:28:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,キャメロン達と付き合うのはやめた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.17,0:28:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも また独りぼっちだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.17,0:28:15.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,アキル\N土曜日だれかと奉仕する？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.68,0:28:17.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ いえ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.01,0:28:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう なら9時半に集合場所で\Nいいかい？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.84,0:28:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕の後\Nマックス兄弟が家に招いてくれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.34,0:28:50.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟これ……？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.55,0:28:51.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,気に入った？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.75,0:28:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.05,0:28:55.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻が いつもカメラ持って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.72,0:28:57.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱中していたんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.72,0:29:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,で 結婚記念日に カメラをくれたんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.16,0:29:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから わたしもとりこだよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.03,0:29:07.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんとに早い\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.26,0:29:11.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻が亡くなってもう\N12年も過ぎたとはね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.20,0:29:12.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.27,0:29:13.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,まあね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.67,0:29:16.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも…今でも写真を？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.07,0:29:19.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ\N撮るのは楽しいよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.24,0:29:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に相手は エホバの創造物だ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.11,0:29:24.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.68,0:29:27.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,独りぼっちじゃないって感じるんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.78,0:29:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.46,0:29:37.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,親友は思いがけないところにいる\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.29,0:29:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,年が違っても\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.40,0:29:44.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟と知り合うにつれて 分かったんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.30,0:29:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデとヨナタンみたいだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.07,0:29:50.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人の友情の基盤は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.14,0:29:54.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,年齢じゃなく エホバへの愛だった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.81,0:29:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして お互いに支え合った\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.25,0:30:04.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,マックス兄弟の助けで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.82,0:30:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も良い霊的な習慣を\N続けることができている\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.33,0:30:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,年が違っても 兄弟と親友になれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.23,0:30:17.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,目を向ければよかったんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.23,0:30:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,目の前にある正しいことに\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.84,0:30:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,年が離れていても 友になれます！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.84,0:30:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の友 それは エホバに\N仕え続けるよう強めてくれる人です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.42,0:30:40.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に成長するとは エホバ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.66,0:30:45.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,また エホバの性格をもっと\Nよく知るということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.56,0:30:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その努力を支えてくれる \N本当の友に出会いたいですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.17,0:30:56.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ことわざで “経験は最良の教師”\Nと言われることがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.37,0:30:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそれは違います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.04,0:31:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,つらい経験をして 苦しんで \N教訓を学ぶことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.08,0:31:09.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,フェルナンド･カシージャス兄弟は\Nメキシコで生まれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.85,0:31:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さい時 家族でアメリカに\N引っ越すことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.19,0:31:21.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は ギャングの影響力が大きい\N地域で成長しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.76,0:31:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い時の経験がもとで 兄弟は人格面で\N大きな問題を抱えるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.30,0:31:32.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,いったいどうやって真理に\N引き寄せられたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.11,0:31:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,見てみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.15,0:31:39.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,暴力を愛していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.11,0:31:41.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,暴力の夢さえ見ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.45,0:31:44.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギャングはわたしの宗教でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.92,0:31:48.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い時から\N矯正施設のお世話になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.22,0:31:50.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初 少年の施設に入れられて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.96,0:31:54.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,暴動を起こしたかどで\Nそこから出されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.13,0:31:55.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは施設にとっても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.90,0:31:59.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,看守や受刑者にとっても\N危険人物とみなされたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.90,0:32:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,残りの刑期を終えるまで\N独房に入れられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.21,0:32:06.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,刑務所を出てきたときには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.07,0:32:09.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前にも増して\N暴力的になっていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.34,0:32:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界一の殺し屋になってやろうと\N思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.12,0:32:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,刑期が終わると\Nメキシコに国外追放になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.16,0:32:24.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも武器を携帯しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.96,0:32:27.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのうち\N悪い仲間と付き合うようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.53,0:32:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガールフレンドも\Nトラブルに巻き込んでしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.57,0:32:35.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,事が収まった後\N彼女が王国会館を見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.57,0:32:38.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼女は子どもの頃\N集会に行っていたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.41,0:32:40.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,今度はわたしも\N引っ張ってゆかれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.61,0:32:42.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,歓迎されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.24,0:32:45.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,オマルと彼の奥さんと\N知り合いになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.31,0:32:50.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから 彼らとの付き合いが始まり\N集会にも行くようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.42,0:32:54.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが オマルが以前\Nライバルのギャングだったことを知った時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.39,0:32:56.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りがこみ上げてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.56,0:32:59.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分から話してくれなかったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.59,0:33:02.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの時は\N“どうやってあいつを連れ出して—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.60,0:33:06.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,“仕返ししてやるか” \N ということばかり考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.83,0:33:11.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,オマルにどんな仕打ちをするか\N一晩中 考えて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.04,0:33:16.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,結局 このまま友達でいることに\Nしたんです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.68,0:33:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 オマルと研究を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.48,0:33:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔の自分を 神が許して下さるわけがない\Nと思っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.15,0:33:30.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも イザヤ 55章7節は\N本当に助けになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.56,0:33:32.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,“邪悪な者はその道を—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.53,0:33:35.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“害を加えようとする者は\N その考えを捨て—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.70,0:33:37.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバのもとに帰れ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.67,0:33:40.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神はその者を憐れんでくださる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.97,0:33:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,学んでゆくにつれ エホバが本当に\N許して下さることが理解できました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.51,0:33:52.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,その頃には もう刑務所に戻るようなことは\Nしない決意でいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.45,0:33:57.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,違法なことをする人たちとの\Nどんな付き合いも断つ決意でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.05,0:33:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,自由になったと感じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.62,0:34:01.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,タバコも大酒もやめて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.96,0:34:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,進歩して伝道者になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.26,0:34:09.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 父が亡くなって\Nまた悪い友達と付き合いはじめ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.46,0:34:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道者を削除になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.60,0:34:16.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンはそういう時を\Nすかさず突いてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.90,0:34:21.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 妻が書類作成のために\N国境を通過しようとした時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.58,0:34:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,車の中に麻薬があると言って\N警備員に止められました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.01,0:34:30.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,車の以前の持ち主が隠していたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.05,0:34:32.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,知る由もありませんでした \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.75,0:34:35.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,後になって妻の嫌疑が晴れてからも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.46,0:34:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもたちは帰してもらえませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.63,0:34:44.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔のやり方に戻るところでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.30,0:34:49.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔の仲間に頼んで\N子どもたちをメキシコに連れ戻すのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.74,0:34:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも この度はエホバに\Nそして兄弟たちにも頼ることにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.78,0:34:59.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは\N定期的に訪問してくださり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.51,0:35:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの保護に頼るよう\N励まし続けてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.45,0:35:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの助けで\N子どもたちは帰してもらえました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.19,0:35:12.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,努力のいることでしたが\N再び伝道者になり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.53,0:35:15.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,数か月後には\Nバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.60,0:35:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔の自分よりずっと幸せです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.27,0:35:21.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,リハビリセンターで伝道した時には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.74,0:35:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもの頃 見たことのある人に\N出会いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:29.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが誰であるかが分かると\Nその人は言いました—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.54,0:35:32.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あんたのせいで おれは引っ越したんだよ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.45,0:35:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“おれを見ると いつも銃で撃ってきた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.05,0:35:38.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと時間がかかりましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.15,0:35:41.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,傷つけるためではなく真理を教え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.09,0:35:43.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の命を得る方法を\N伝えるために来た—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.93,0:35:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ということを納得してもらえました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.43,0:35:50.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう暴力的な人間ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.40,0:35:53.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから特別な割り当てもいただいています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.87,0:35:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕の僕として2年間仕えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.31,0:35:59.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,会計の奉仕もしていて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.27,0:36:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔の自分だったら\N盗んでいたお金を扱っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.78,0:36:07.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,園芸で生計を立てています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.11,0:36:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今はナイフではなく\N園芸道具を持ち歩いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.05,0:36:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ピストルをすきの刃に\Nもしくは芝刈り機に打ち変えたわけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.06,0:36:23.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,偉大な神にお仕えできて幸福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.90,0:36:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛と気遣いの神\N許して下さる方にです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.51,0:36:35.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,フェルナンド兄弟は 家族と一緒に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.14,0:36:39.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,メキシコにある英語会衆で\N奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.75,0:36:42.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は自分の経験から— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.12,0:36:48.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,“最良の教師”は経験ではなく\Nエホバだと悟りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.56,0:36:50.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに従ってください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.73,0:36:54.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,つらい経験を背負って\N苦しむ必要はありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.73,0:36:57.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはあなたのためを思い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.20,0:37:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの“益”になることを\N教えているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.97,0:37:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,改訂版のエレミヤ 17章13節\Nを見ると分かりますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.01,0:37:15.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えようとしない人たちの名は\N塵の中に書かれていることになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.78,0:37:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さん エホバと共に\N将来を築いていってください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.19,0:37:25.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら\Nエホバは皆さんの名前を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.26,0:37:29.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 4章3節と\N啓示 3章5節で述べられている— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.26,0:37:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“命の書”に書き留めてくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.70,0:37:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,このプログラムの最初のほうで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.81,0:37:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に将来を築いている\N若い人たちが出てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.61,0:37:47.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような若い人たちの努力は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.88,0:37:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織にどんな良い影響を\N与えているでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.05,0:37:54.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つの例を見ましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.66,0:37:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク州ウォーウィック世界本部\Nの建設の様子です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.40,0:38:05.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人は4年足らずで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.10,0:38:10.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,14万9000平方メートルの\N建物を建てました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.10,0:38:19.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,2万7035人の自発奉仕者のうち\N3247人は19歳から25歳でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.91,0:38:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,経験を積んだベテランの兄弟姉妹だけを\N必要とするプロジェクトだと思っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.32,0:38:30.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも すぐにそれは間違いだと\N気づきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.89,0:38:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,仕事量が多いので 若い力が\Nどうしても必要でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.70,0:38:40.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,年長者と若者が交じってウォーウィック\Nのプロジェクトを助けてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.84,0:38:43.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,年長者は技術と経験があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.64,0:38:50.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,若者にはエネルギーや体力 また\N粘り強く行なう勤勉さがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.24,0:38:53.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,キッチンや夜の警備の仕事もあれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.11,0:38:58.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,朝5時に マイナス12度の中で\Nコンクリートを打つ仕事もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.29,0:39:03.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,どの仕事も謙遜に 喜んで行なう姿は\N際立っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.36,0:39:08.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い兄弟姉妹が大勢 \N通いの奉仕のために移動して来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.43,0:39:14.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも精力的に働き 晩になっても元気で\N次の日の工程に間に合いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.94,0:39:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのパワーに圧倒されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.44,0:39:21.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは若者を愛しておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.21,0:39:26.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜んで彼らに投資し 訓練し \N組織の一員になるのをお望みなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.78,0:39:28.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを何度も見てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.62,0:39:33.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,高い技術を差し出す若者が大勢います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.12,0:39:35.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし たとえ専門技術があっても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.89,0:39:42.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,能力以上に 謙遜さがないと \Nエホバは用いることはされないでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.36,0:39:44.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らは進んで調整しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.77,0:39:47.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,その益を実際見てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.54,0:39:50.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは単なるウォーウィックの建設\Nプロジェクトではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.87,0:39:53.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのため霊的に建てるプロジェクト\Nであることを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.97,0:39:57.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも若い奉仕者たちも\N分かりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.65,0:40:01.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの霊が彼らに働いているのが\N分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.32,0:40:04.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,あっという間に円熟するんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.62,0:40:09.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした若い兄弟たちは次世代の長老や\N旅行する監督になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.56,0:40:14.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでの貢献は高く評価され \N称賛されるものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.06,0:40:19.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らはベテル奉仕がもたらした良い影響\Nについてよく語っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.37,0:40:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,またこの世の日常の事柄に気を\N散らされたくないとも言っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.54,0:40:31.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,このプロジェクトやベテルで学んだ\N技術を使ってください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.58,0:40:34.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんが必要なのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.38,0:40:40.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,高い霊性を保ち 築き上げる交わりを\N持ってください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.86,0:40:43.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,最も価値ある人生とは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.02,0:40:46.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,偉大な陶器師エホバの手に \N自分をゆだねて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.23,0:40:51.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ここにわたしがおります！わたしを\N 遣わしてください”と言えることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.27,0:40:53.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,確信して言えますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.17,0:40:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の将来をエホバと共に築くことに\N決して後悔はしないでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.48,0:41:08.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い兄弟姉妹は世界本部の\N建設プロジェクトに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.82,0:41:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に大きく貢献してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.82,0:41:19.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて ウォーウィックとウォールキルの\N建設プロジェクトについてですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.09,0:41:22.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,実はこのプロジェクトを\N進めるための資金は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.73,0:41:27.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界的な業のための寄付から賄われた\Nわけではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.67,0:41:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんの寄付は 世界中の野外の\N活動を支えるために用いられています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.64,0:41:39.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウォーウィックとウォールキルの\N巨大建設プロジェクトは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.41,0:41:44.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブルックリンの資産を売却した\N資金で賄われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.15,0:41:49.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 場所を変えただけ\Nということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.42,0:41:51.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブルックリンの資産を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.13,0:41:52.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウォーウィック ウォールキルの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.63,0:41:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この美しい施設に交換した\Nということになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.57,0:41:59.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,お伝えしておきたいと思いますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.97,0:42:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体はウォーウィックの新しい本部で\N過ごす毎日を本当に楽しんでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.17,0:42:11.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人たちも 年長の人たちも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.41,0:42:15.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちのため懸命に\N働いてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.42,0:42:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心から感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.22,0:42:25.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 2章20節から23節で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.96,0:42:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロはテモテについて\Nこう言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.46,0:42:32.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方のことを真に気づかう—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.53,0:42:36.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼のような気持ちの者は \N わたしにとってほかにいないのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.50,0:42:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ほかの者はみな自分の益を求め—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.81,0:42:41.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,“キリスト･イエスの益を\N 求めていません”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.48,0:42:46.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかしあなた方は 彼が自分自身に\N ついて実証した事柄を知っています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.58,0:42:52.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“つまり 良いたよりを推し進めるため\N 子供が父親に対するようにして—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.02,0:42:55.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしと共に奴隷として\N 仕えてくれたことです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.69,0:43:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そのようなわけで わたしはこの人を\N 遣わしたいと希望しているのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.96,0:43:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは 若いテモテを\N深く愛していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.43,0:43:09.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは テモテが自分のことを\N後回しにし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.47,0:43:12.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国のために懸命に働いていたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.97,0:43:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体も 若い兄弟姉妹に対して\N同じように感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.38,0:43:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんは 与えられたそれぞれの\N神権的な責任を懸命に果たしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.96,0:43:31.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,プログラムの最初のほうで見たように\N全時間奉仕には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.53,0:43:34.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな分野があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.23,0:43:40.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて 地元で生じる必要のため\N自分を役立てることも大切な奉仕です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.47,0:43:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような奉仕をして \N王国を第一に求めることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.37,0:43:52.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 米国テキサス州の\Nサン･アントニオで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.41,0:43:59.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,2万人以上が出席する \Nとても大きな大会が計画されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.79,0:44:02.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 会場から提供された\N椅子の数は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.99,0:44:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席者の3分の1ほどしか\Nありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.43,0:44:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちはどうやって椅子を\N確保したでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.00,0:44:14.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこには エホバの助け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.74,0:44:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして たくさんの若い人たちの\N働きがありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.04,0:44:28.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要が知らされた時 \Nどうしたらいいんだろうと思いました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.12,0:44:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,圧倒されました！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.35,0:44:33.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,びっくりしました！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.69,0:44:35.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初に求められたのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.39,0:44:40.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,6000から8000脚の椅子の\N保管場所を確保することでした \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.63,0:44:44.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある姉妹が経営している所で\Nオーナーが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.47,0:44:50.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバの証人の組織と契約できるなら\N 1年間無料で使ってよい”と言ったので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.67,0:44:53.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの祝福を感じました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.14,0:44:56.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラック トラック またトラック \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.34,0:45:03.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,椅子を降ろし ひとつずつ分けて修理し \N掃除し パレットに重ねて戻し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.18,0:45:05.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,またトラックに入れました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.82,0:45:09.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 倉庫に入れたものはまだ半分です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.49,0:45:15.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて サン・アントニオにある会衆に\N椅子を貸してくれるよう依頼しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.36,0:45:18.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,3000脚の椅子です \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.23,0:45:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の規模が大きくなったので \Nもっと椅子が必要です \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.00,0:45:24.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでサン･アントニオ周辺の会衆から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.37,0:45:29.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,6000脚を自発奉仕者の手によって\N集めることができました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.24,0:45:35.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,これについて祈り 奉仕者が募られ \N最初から大きな協力が得られました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.65,0:45:40.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たちにこの件について話すと\Nすぐにみんなが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.09,0:45:43.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,“仕事を早引きして手伝います”\N と言いました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.42,0:45:46.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに自分たちの予定を調整しました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.49,0:45:50.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,できることは何でもしたかったからです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.30,0:45:54.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの会衆が一端を担えたのは\N貴重な機会でした \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.94,0:45:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切なチャンスを与えてくださった\Nエホバに感謝しています \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.77,0:46:06.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろんなカラーの椅子がありました \N緑 赤 ブラウン 青—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.71,0:46:11.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,オレンジ色の椅子も70脚ほどあり\N全て運びました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.72,0:46:14.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも問題はサイズです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.46,0:46:16.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな違っていました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.56,0:46:19.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうやってきれいに並べるかが\N課題でした \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.99,0:46:23.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバの民としてできる\Nと思いました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.83,0:46:26.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの奉仕者が集まりました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.17,0:46:27.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして成し遂げたのです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.90,0:46:33.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めて会う兄弟姉妹たちと友情を\N深められたのは 素晴らしいことです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.11,0:46:37.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆が一致して働く意欲に満ちていました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.38,0:46:43.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,会場を使うかどうかにかかわらず \Nすべての人がエホバのために働きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.12,0:46:45.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かにエホバは秩序の神です \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.82,0:46:48.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにベストを差し出せて 満足です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.86,0:46:51.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 127編1節に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.43,0:46:54.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバご自身が\N 家を建てるのでなければ—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.26,0:46:58.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,“建てる者たちがそのために骨折って\N 働いても無駄である”とあります \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.77,0:47:03.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべてがスムーズに運ぶのは エホバの\Nみ手と祝福があるおかげなのです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.90,0:47:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような組織は\Nほかには決してありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.08,0:47:17.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人たちが 自分の時間を用いて \N心をこめて働く様子は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.68,0:47:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても良い証言になっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.59,0:47:29.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言 20章29節にある通り\N“若者の美しさはその力”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.43,0:47:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さんは エホバの前で\N良い名を得たいと願い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.50,0:47:36.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の力を用いておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.90,0:47:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは立派なことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.97,0:47:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,外国語の区域で奉仕したいと\N思ったことはありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.31,0:47:49.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしかしたら 今いる巡回区でも\N必要があるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.92,0:47:54.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの目標は 国や人種や\N言語を越えて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.09,0:47:58.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての人に 神の言葉から\N良いニュースを伝えることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.66,0:48:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのため組織は 世界中で\N言語訓練コースを開いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.63,0:48:10.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,フアン･カルロス･チャコン兄弟は\Nエクアドルで急速に拡大している—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.34,0:48:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,シュワール語の区域で \N特別開拓者として奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.08,0:48:24.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は最近 地元の支部で開かれる\N言語訓練コースに出席しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.22,0:48:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして教訓者として 言語を学びたい\Nと願う奉仕者たちを助けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.54,0:48:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう言われたことがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.61,0:48:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これは悪魔の言葉だ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.24,0:48:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,忘れるべきだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.58,0:48:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何の役にも立たない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.72,0:49:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバにとって\N重要でない国民はいません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.33,0:49:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはシュワール族の大集落がある\Nエクアドルのジャングルで育ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.74,0:49:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの土着の言語同様\Nシュワール語は非常に複雑です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.58,0:49:32.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,野外ではもっと多くの働き人が必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.42,0:49:37.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 言語の基礎知識を教えて\N援助し 励まさなければ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.16,0:49:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この区域に来ることは困難です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.06,0:49:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは言語クラスの教訓者の\Nセミナーに招待されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.11,0:50:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこには 16の異なった言語グループから\N58名の生徒が来ていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.85,0:50:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんは革新的に言語を\N教える方法を学ぶことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.32,0:50:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは実際に効果のある\N素晴らしい教え方を学んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.47,0:50:24.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,教訓者によると\Nユーモアがあれば脳は活性化され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.37,0:50:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,頭の中で関連付けが\N容易になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.15,0:50:39.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.42,0:50:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,絵を描くときは小さな子どものようでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.56,0:50:47.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,うまく描けませんでしたけど\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.73,0:50:50.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,場面を描いて \N大きな身振りをしながら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.30,0:50:52.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,現地語を使います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.27,0:50:54.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,場面を演じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.84,0:50:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,少しづつ新しい言語を使った\N場面にしていきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.41,0:51:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく来られました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.71,0:51:07.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,今から\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.38,0:51:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出かけてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.23,0:51:21.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安なことですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.06,0:51:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,やったことがないんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.36,0:51:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めてなんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.54,0:51:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,言語を教えた経験がありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.08,0:51:45.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安でいっぱいですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.65,0:51:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがおられるなら\Nすべてのことが可能だと分かっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.46,0:52:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,シュワール語の言語コースに\N皆さんようこそ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.35,0:52:20.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,教えられた技術は\N道具箱に似ていて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.19,0:52:22.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに注意深く学び—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.29,0:52:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれの状況にどう当てはめるかを\N理解しなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.40,0:52:39.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,区域では 人々が神の名前を知ったときに \Nその目が輝くのを見ることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.31,0:52:42.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々は真理を学ぶ必要が大いにあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.88,0:52:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを知るだけでも ここに来て\N奉仕を続ける動機が強まります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.26,0:53:00.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はわたしたちを造られたので\Nお見捨てにはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.93,0:53:04.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもわたしたちのことを考え\N愛してくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.60,0:53:06.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前は知りませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.97,0:53:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に神の言葉が理解できて\N今は幸せです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.41,0:53:18.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆から遠く離れた\N孤立した群れにいても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.78,0:53:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻と私はエホバを\N毎日身近に感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.12,0:53:29.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 エホバはこれら小さな群れに\N目を留め 注意を払っておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.42,0:53:31.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなに小さくてもです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.76,0:53:36.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々に良い心と神に仕えたい\Nとの願いがあれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.03,0:53:40.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは助けるために\N働き人を遣わされます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.37,0:53:45.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして わたしたちは本当に\N心からエホバにこう申し上げます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.74,0:53:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ありがとうございます　エホバ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.32,0:54:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,年齢に関係なく エホバの組織の中で\Nできることはたくさんあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.02,0:54:07.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,状況ゆえに できることが\N限られているかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.33,0:54:11.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバは分かっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.20,0:54:15.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教を拡大し \Nエホバと共に永遠に歩みたいと願い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.97,0:54:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが努力しているのを見て \N高く評価してくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.08,0:54:26.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のミュージックビデオが伝えるのは\Nそのメッセージです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.61,0:54:28.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,タイトルは— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.45,0:54:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“未来を築く エホバと共に” です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.03,0:54:44.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこに向かうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.97,0:54:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何を選べばいい？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.40,0:54:52.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,この旅路の先に\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.04,0:54:57.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が待っている？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.98,0:55:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもわかる 確かなことは\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.25,0:55:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう エホバのために生きる\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.00,0:55:19.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ何かに 満たされても\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.83,0:55:24.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,忘れない エホバをずっと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.57,0:55:32.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜ばせること 今この手で\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.61,0:55:37.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな小さな輝きでも\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.58,0:55:42.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひとつずつ 重ねてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.02,0:55:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来をエホバと 築いてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.46,0:55:54.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,時々 出会う\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.77,0:55:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“成功って何か？”と\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.04,0:56:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,脚色＜いろづけ＞された明日を 見せられてる\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.11,0:56:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも揺れない 心に決めた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.02,0:56:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの誓い 今も\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ誰かが 迷わせようと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.24,0:56:33.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,悔やまない 僕らはきっと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.97,0:56:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,夜明けにきらめく 露のように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.55,0:56:47.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな小さな輝きでも\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.32,0:56:51.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひとつずつ 重ねてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.72,0:56:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来をエホバと 築いてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.53,0:57:04.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりのない 旅がある\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.37,0:57:09.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,生きてる意味 感じてる\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.21,0:57:13.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう エホバとの友情に\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.38,0:57:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,勝るものなど 何もない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.14,0:57:43.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ嵐が 押し寄せようと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.11,0:57:47.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れない この先ずっと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.28,0:57:55.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,岩の上に立つ 家のように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.22,0:58:00.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな小さな輝きでも\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.39,0:58:04.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひとつずつ 重ねてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.50,0:58:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来をエホバと 築いてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.24,0:58:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来をエホバと 築いてゆく\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.26,0:58:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に心が奮い立ちますね！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.53,0:58:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に未来を築きましょう！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.77,0:58:41.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人たちみんなが \N今月のプログラムにある—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.77,0:58:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このメッセージを\N心に留めてくれるよう願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.51,0:58:49.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈って 宣教を拡大するため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.44,0:58:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分には何ができるだろう \Nと考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.22,0:58:58.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが持つ一番大切なもの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.08,0:59:00.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの友情— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.29,0:59:03.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,それをしっかりと\N守り続けてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.76,0:59:05.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんの敵がいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.49,0:59:10.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも もっとたくさんの友がいることを\N決して忘れないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.43,0:59:15.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵は サタン 悪霊 この世です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.74,0:59:19.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,では あなたの側にはだれがいますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.14,0:59:21.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たち 姉妹たち— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.41,0:59:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体が共にいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.28,0:59:27.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使たちも共にいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.15,0:59:33.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,復活して 不滅性を与えられている\N油そそがれた人たちも共にいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.42,0:59:36.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスがあなたと一緒です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.59,0:59:40.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして エホバがあなたのそばに\Nおられるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.96,0:59:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんながそばにいることを \N決して忘れないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.04,0:59:53.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,プログラムの最後に \N昨年4月フランスのパリで開かれた—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.81,0:59:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別大会からのあいさつを\Nお伝えしたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.31,1:00:03.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,教育委員会の援助者\Nケニス･フローディン兄弟と共に—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.15,1:00:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会に出席することができました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.59,1:00:10.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,プログラムのほとんどは\Nフランス語で提供されましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.99,1:00:13.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中から来た代表者たちのため—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.66,1:00:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,プログラムはクロアチア語 英語 \Nポーランド語に同時通訳されました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.57,1:00:25.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大会で 71人の姉妹たちと\N41人の兄弟たちが—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.14,1:00:29.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの献身を表わして \N水のバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.54,1:00:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,うれしいですね\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.38,1:00:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最年長は80歳の姉妹 \N最年少は10歳でした\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.05,1:00:43.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い兄弟姉妹たちは \Nバプテスマを受けるまでに—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.12,1:00:46.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな問題を乗り越えてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.06,1:00:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,4人の兄弟姉妹は 両親とも\Nエホバの証人ではない中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.10,1:00:57.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの若い人たちは 学校での圧力を\N受けながら進歩してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.37,1:01:01.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが喜ばれないことを\Nさせようとする圧力です\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.11,1:01:03.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人の若い実の兄弟がいました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.68,1:01:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは以前 \N暴力的なゲームをしていたようです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.85,1:01:13.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 聖書を研究し \N個人的な関心を示してもらううちに—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.42,1:01:16.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが暴力を\Nどう見ているかが分かり—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.26,1:01:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの関係を成長させようと\N生活を調整しました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.43,1:01:26.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマという最初のステップを\N踏むことで 兄弟たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.37,1:01:31.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に将来を築きたいと\N願っていることを示しました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.97,1:01:37.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの友情を成長させてゆくため\Nベストを尽くしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.24,1:01:42.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば エホバは是認し \Nほほえんでくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.65,1:01:47.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たち \N皆さんを心から愛しています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.92,1:01:52.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の世界本部からお送りした \NJW Broadcastingでした\N
